
cURL used for transferring data from/to a server, offers many functions such as:
- http post
- ftp post
- user authentication
- file transfer
- proxy support
- cookies
- SSL connections 

#---------HTTP GET METHOD---------
used to request data from a specified resource

#HTTP GET command example (json)
curl -H "Content-Type:application/json" -H "Accept:application/json" -X GET http://google.com
#-H specifies a Header
#-X specifies the request

#--------HTTP POST METHOD----------
used to send data to server, create/update resource

#HTTP POST example
curl --data "name=value1&name2=value2" https://www.packtpub.com
#--data - POST request

#uploading a file
curl -T "{a}" https://packtpub.com
